In [5]:
feature_matrix = pd.merge(symptoms, demographics, how='outer', left_index=True, right_index=True)

Dependent variable is a mini time-series per patient. How do we work with this? Simplest is to take a representative statistic like max or mean, even though this means discarding information. Another option would be to take the diff between min and max (positive or negative depending on which came first). Another possibility would be to train separate models per patient and then aggregate them.

numeric_cols = [
    "Total Pre Treatment Depression Score",
    "Years lived at residence",
    "Months lived at residence",
    "Number of relatives living with patient",
    "Number of friends living with patient",
    "Total number of persons in household",
    "Years of schooling completed",
    "target",
]
numeric_cols = [{v: k for k, v in var_names.items()}[x] for x in numeric_cols]
In [16]:
categ_cols = list(set(feature_matrix.columns).difference(numeric_cols))

Some decisions about the data:

  • Fill NaN values with the mode. Could have also gone with a special numeric value as a category for "missing". Could also have done imputation since not too much missing data.
  • Decided not to standardise the numeric columns. Can help with interpreting the model, but for now we're just looking for correlations with the target
In [17]:
for c in feature_matrix.columns:
    feature_matrix[c] = feature_matrix[c].fillna(feature_matrix[c].mode()[0])

In [22]:
for col in X.columns:
    if '_' in col:
        name, value = col.split('_')
        X = X.rename(columns={col: var_names[name] + ' = ' + value})
    else:
        X = X.rename(columns={col: var_names[col]})

We used LASSO (L1) regularisation in the logistic regression model, which is good for feature selection since it zeroes a lot of the weights. We can extract the features with higher weights in this model.

Summary¶

The random forest model seems like the best, since it has the highest score, but not by much. It would be very helpful to talk to a domain expert and try figure out some priors about which features are actually valuable.
